[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T23:10:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a computer screen with a blue exclamation point on it and an error box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VV3Byi3KQMfkkkP5dGXBIMIX9Vk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415321/akrales_220309_4977_0232.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fWciDX\">AMD is looking into a potential cyberattack. A threat actor that goes by the alias \u201cIntelBroker\u201d is selling data that it claims was obtained from an AMD.com breach this month, <a href=\"https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/amd-investigates-breach-after-data-for-sale-on-hacking-forum/\"><em>BleepingComputer</em> reports</a>, and the company confirmed in a statement that it\u2019s looking into the purported theft. IntelBroker claims that the data for sale includes future products, employee databases, and customer databases.</p>\n<p id=\"aneOWN\">\u201cWe are aware of a cybercriminal organization clai", "id": 735906, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181406/amd-investigating-claims-stolen-company-data-sale-intelbroker", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AMD is investigating claims of stolen company data", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T23:00:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Someone holding Haptique RS90 remote\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wbY6QkzzWElz9zgZQ_2D2H8OpDQ=/0x2:2048x1367/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415309/haptique_rs90.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>One remote to rule them all (but in the darkness, you probably still can\u2019t find them).</em> | Photo: Cantata</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gJ6ser\">Universal remotes might be on a comeback tour if devices like <a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/cantata/haptique-rs90-a-true-universal-remote-controller\">Cantata\u2019s Haptique RS90 and RS90X</a> actually materialize and are as good as advertised. The connected remote purports to double as a comprehensive smart home controller, but it\u2019s merely a Kickstarter hopeful for now. Serial remoters (remotees?) have pledged more than $300,00, with less than $10,000 needed to fully fund the project as of writing, and there\u2019s currently an estimated ship date of August 2024.</p>\n<div id=\"RQc", "id": 735907, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181245/cantata-haptique-rs90-rs90x-universal-remote-smart-home-controller", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This universal remote wants to control your smart home sans hub", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T22:44:32+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the Ndivia logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EjAzJLNy2x24JIgeRDg9R39gt-4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415282/STK083_B_NVIDIA_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xZk7B3\">Less than two weeks after Nvidia <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/5/24172363/nvidia-apple-market-cap-valuation-trillion-ai\">jumped Apple</a> in terms of its overall valuation, the GPU maker has now passed Microsoft to stand as the world\u2019s most valuable company based on the chips it makes that are key to powering a boom in generative AI technology. </p>\n<p id=\"UNTxr1\">At the close of trading on Tuesday, its share price stood at $135.58, up $4.60 from the previous day and pushing its market cap to $3.335 trillion. That\u2019s more than Microsoft ($3.32 trillion), Apple ($3.29 trillion), and Google ($2.17 trillion). Nvidia\u2019s shares split 10-for-1 after June 7th, lowerin", "id": 735908, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181393/nvidia-most-valuable-company-microsoft-apple-google", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nvidia overtakes Microsoft as the world\u2019s most valuable company", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T22:21:54+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y6HP-4opvfs3fZqNMbM5nkR8dPE=/0x1:4143x2763/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415248/1036716180.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Chomsky often was critical of the media.</em> | Photo by Heuler Andrey / AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"6TFEs9\">Everyone dies eventually, and famed linguist Noam Chomsky will be no different \u2014 but at the time of this writing, he is alive. And, sadly, his wife is explaining to people that reports of his death are \u201cfalse,\u201d <a href=\"https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/noam-chomskys-wife-reports-famed-linguists-death-false-111230881\">according to <em>The Associated Press</em></a>.</p>\n<p id=\"SgS28y\">Chomsky, 95, has been hospitalized in Brazil as he recovers from a stroke he had last year, <a href=\"https://apnews.com/article/noam-chomsky-hospitalized-stroke-recovery-brazil-4fb6782abf6a7b6d0bbb30cefa05cede\">the <em>AP</em> reported earlier thi", "id": 735696, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181373/noam-chomsky-not-dead-yet", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Noam Chomsky isn\u2019t dead yet", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T22:05:44+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mQJTF4fJ8JHd6dgVrGmbJ7OMknQ=/255x0:2625x1580/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415220/Screen_Shot_2024_06_17_at_10.57.59_AM.0.png\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OSHB0Y\">Last week, AI startup Luma posted a series of videos created using its new video-generating tool Dream Machine, which the company describes as a \u201chighly scalable and efficient transformer model trained directly on videos.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"VxMmvD\">The only problem? At about 57 seconds in, the Dream Machine-generated <a href=\"https://x.com/LumaLabsAI/status/1800921393321934915\">trailer for <em>Monster Camp</em></a> \u2014 an animated story about furry creatures journeying to a sleepaway camp \u2014 features a slightly AI-smudged but still recognizable Mike Wazowski from Pixar\u2019s <em>Monsters, Inc.</em> Many people noticed that multiple characters and its overall aesthetic look borrowed from the franchise, and the questions quickly started pouring in.</p>\n<d", "id": 735697, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181375/luma-ai-monster-camp-monsters-inc-pixar", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Luma promoted its AI video generator with some very familiar incorporated monsters", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T21:17:41+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/WzEMr-282QDa_wqFo3uf1SMA0ew=/0x419:2160x1859/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415143/Philips_Hue_Twilight_in_white___lifestyle.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Hue\u2019s new Twilight bedside lamp costs $280.</em> | Image: Philips Hue</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"2WyvDl\">Following <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/15/24179119/philips-hue-smart-lamp-twilight-solo-lightstrip\">leaks last week</a>, smart lighting company Philips Hue has confirmed it has a new sunrise lamp called <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.philips-hue.com%2Fnewlaunches&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F6%2F18%2F24181145%2Fphilips-hue-new-products-twilight-bedside-lamp-price-release-date\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Twilight</a>. The company also announced several other new products, including a less expens", "id": 735297, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181145/philips-hue-new-products-twilight-bedside-lamp-price-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hue launches a pricey new sunrise lamp", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T20:44:44+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A fading Wifi symbol above the United States.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6Hk8eQaDENXWwNfvAvDFdtpE_nc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415054/STK451_Internet_Service_Providers_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photo from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5scT52\">Don\u2019t hold your breath for a resurgence of government internet subsidies. Republicans and Democrats can\u2019t seem to agree on a way forward to fund the program, and passing such bills will only get more difficult as Election Day inches closer.</p>\n<p id=\"UmNvu2\">Democrats and Republicans have introduced dueling bills to reauthorize the Federal Communications Commission\u2019s spectrum auctions, where the agency doles out access to frequencies that can be used to carry wireless signals. But the Democratic bill that has been repeatedly delayed in committee specifically seeks to fund a now-defunct internet subs", "id": 735298, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181011/spectrum-legislation-postponed-affordable-connectivity-program", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "An effort to fund an internet subsidy program just got thwarted again", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T20:26:22+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The lid of the Framework Laptop 13 (AMD) seen from the right side.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GzaJpQV_kTBpchZruCDxO6oGmmo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73415022/236795_Framework_Laptop_13__AMD__AKrales_0221.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"W84MCj\">What if your laptop didn\u2019t need a processor from an established brand like Intel or AMD? What if it didn\u2019t even rely on proprietary paid architectures like Arm and x86? RISC-V is one of the answers to those questions \u2014 it\u2019s free for anyone to use! \u2014 and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/23/24138475/framework-laptop-product-categories-new\">modular computer company Framework</a> has just decided to welcome RISC-V into its laptop lineup.</p>\n<p id=\"NYMkQR\">Specifically, Framework has partnered with DeepComputing, <a href=\"https://deepcomputing.io/worlds-first-risc-v-laptop-gets-a-massive-u", "id": 735299, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181278/framework-laptop-risc-v-laptop-isa-arm-amd-intel-x86", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Framework Laptop 13 is about to become one of the world\u2019s first RISC-V laptops", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T19:38:50+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Fisker CEO Henrik Fisker\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jkchs9iCF24L5vc-Z5QHbZgyksY=/0x0:4545x3030/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414899/1575080703.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Fisker CEO Henrik Fisker.</em> | Photo by Frederic J. Brown / AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LxbsJi\">Earlier today, Fisker finally did what has <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/1/24087516/fisker-ev-earnings-layoff-going-concern-warning\">seemed inevitable</a> these past few turbulent months: declared bankruptcy. </p>\n<p id=\"TBBmUL\">\u201cLike other companies in the electric vehicle industry, we have faced various market and macroeconomic headwinds that have impacted our ability to operate efficiently,\u201d the company said in a statement. \u201cAfter evaluating all options for our business, we determined that proceeding with a sale of our assets under Chapter 11 is the most viable path forward for the company.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"XHrerm\">Fo", "id": 734910, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181228/fisker-bankrupt-chapter-11-ev-ocean-tesla-playbook-musk", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Fisker tried to out Tesla Tesla, and now it\u2019s bankrupt", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T19:20:05+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Android 15 logo on a light green background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/h-pn9E-tMXIJtBAz_lPqaBOl_DQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414891/247030_Android_15_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>One step closer to a final release in the fall.</em> | Image: The Verge / Android</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aZwlgm\">It\u2019s beta software season, baby. Google is releasing Android 15\u2019s third beta today, taking it one step closer to its final release. With this update, it reaches platform stability, meaning that APIs are finalized and developers can start testing their apps with this near-final version. Not much appears to have changed since the last beta dropped, but that doesn\u2019t mean there aren\u2019t a few interesting tidbits to still uncover.</p>\n<p id=\"o7pgM8\">In <a href=\"https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2024/06/the-third-beta-of-android-15.html\">a blog post announcing the new beta</a>, Google hi", "id": 734911, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181150/android-15-beta-3-platform-stability-passkeys", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Android 15 just reached a major milestone", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T19:15:24+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A teacher holds the Sphero Bolt Plus robot in their hand out toward the camera.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oELsA0DG74_4YlLc3LL5wFYQ6LQ=/0x0:1200x800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414881/sphero_bolt_plus_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Sphero Bolt Plus\u2019 new full-color screen can help kids troubleshoot their code.</em> | Image: Sphero</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Hbqwqa\">Sphero has updated its RC Bolt robotic ball with a higher-resolution LCD screen, providing improved visual feedback that promises to make the <a href=\"https://sphero.com/blogs/press-releases/sphero-launches-sphero-bolt\">new Bolt Plus</a> a better STEM tool for teaching kids the fundamentals of programming. </p>\n<p id=\"LXeOKH\">Originally making a name for itself with a simple remote control ball that could be steered using a smartphone, Sphero eventually found massive success by leveraging its technology to create a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.", "id": 734912, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181166/sphero-bolt-plus-toy-programming-stem-robot", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sphero\u2019s Bolt Plus robot has a screen parents would want their kids to look at", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T19:01:10+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of Whee.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VxjLBbeFi18JSt26vVlY-bLZLmg=/0x35:809x574/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414851/unnamed_3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: TikTok</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"nvxBNR\">TikTok recently launched a new Instagram-like photo-sharing app called Whee, as <a href=\"https://x.com/ArtemR/status/1802925374252482907\">spotted by</a> <em>Android Police</em> and APKMirror founder Artem Russakovskii.</p>\n<p id=\"2RhOHI\">TikTok is explicitly positioning Whee as an app for sharing photos with only your closest friends. \u201cCapture and share real-life photos that only your friends can see, allowing you to be your most authentic self,\u201d <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.bytedance.snail&amp;pli=1\">according to Whee\u2019s Google Play description</a>. \u201cWhee is the best place for close friends to share life moments.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"FCCylO\">Screenshots of the app listing feature th", "id": 734552, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181215/tiktok-whee-app-instagram", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "TikTok is copying Instagram again with Whee", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T18:49:43+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshots of the Butterflies AI app.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4GM3wy8C3TH-BI9DkXHSdivNWgw=/840x231:2227x1156/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414807/Group_Shot.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Butterflies AI.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZkLgqr\">So far, generative AI has been mostly confined to chatbots like ChatGPT. Startups like Character.AI and Replika <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/4/24144763/ai-chatbot-friends-character-teens\">are seeing early traction</a> by making chatbots more like companions. But what happens when you dump a bunch of AI characters into something that looks like Instagram and let them talk to each other?</p>\n<p id=\"Tt9Dc0\">That\u2019s the idea behind Butterflies, one of the most provocative \u2014 and, at times, unsettling \u2014 takes on social media that I\u2019ve seen in quite a while. After a private beta period with tens of thousands of users, the app is now available for free in the <a href", "id": 734553, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181196/butterflies-app-ai-chatbots-social-media", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AIs are coming for social networks", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T18:30:49+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person playing a PS5 game via Remote Play on the PlayStation Portal.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cFihDSc4bLvMtifpyJiQNF8joPo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414774/111323_PlayStation_Portal_ADiBenedetto_0005.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Portal is getting a very slow trickle of software updates.</em> | Photo by Antonio G. Di Benedetto / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ULMost\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24012547/sony-playstation-portal-handheld-remote-player-ps5-chiaki-review\">PlayStation Portal</a> is getting a couple of modest features it should have had in the first place. Sony <a href=\"https://blog.playstation.com/2024/06/18/new-playstation-portal-remote-player-system-software-update-releases-tomorrow/\">announced on its PlayStation Blog</a> that a software update for its handheld remote player will allow users to connect their devices to public Wi-Fi networks that require sig", "id": 734554, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181118/sony-playstation-portal-public-wifi-battery-touchpads-software-update", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sony\u2019s PlayStation Portal update adds public Wi-Fi support", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T18:29:46+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A man leaps to hit a tennis ball on an Olympic court. Another man is crouching on the court in front of him.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yric9wDSk9GBmpYsD9xagVsu7SI=/0x0:5259x3506/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414765/1234310977.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>New Zealand\u2019s Marcus Daniell (TOP) and Michael Venus compete against USA\u2019s Austin Krajicek and Tennys Sandgren during their Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games men\u2019s doubles tennis match for the bronze medal at the Ariake Tennis Park in Tokyo on July 30th, 2021.</em> | Photo by Vincenzo Pinto / AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8fOXhN\">Athletes are raising concerns about how extreme heat might affect the Summer Olympic Games in Paris, according to a new <a href=\"https://basis.org.uk/2024/06/18/rings-of-fire-ii-extreme-heat-at-the-2024-olympics-2/\">report</a>. They\u2019re worried that soaring temperatures pose serious health risks to competitors and spectators, ", "id": 734555, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181004/summer-paris-olympics-heatwave-athletes-report", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Athletes sound warning about extreme heat at Summer Olympics", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T17:57:43+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Red artwork of the Adobe brand logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UI2tCt8yjepgJ0sF0cFgaroWoME=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414674/acastro_STK124_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wO2kje\">For the past couple of weeks, Adobe has faced <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/7/24173838/adobe-tos-update-firefly-generative-ai-trust\">intense backlash over changes</a> to its terms of service agreement \u2014 and now, it\u2019s trying to patch things up. On Tuesday, Adobe announced <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adobe.com%2Flegal%2Fterms.html&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F6%2F18%2F24181001%2Fadobe-updated-terms-of-service-wont-train-ai-on-work\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">a tweaked version</a> of its terms of service agreement that", "id": 734105, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181001/adobe-updated-terms-of-service-wont-train-ai-on-work", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Adobe\u2019s new terms of service say it won\u2019t use your work to train AI", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T16:56:29+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An artist\u2019s conceptual illustration of a Netflix House building at dusk.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UtT5raR3ZdgQDtTcN99rQ-gjWb8=/0x0:1012x675/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414520/netflix_house.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>An artist\u2019s concept of what the Netflix House retail destinations could look like.</em> | Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XeEOwM\">Today, Netflix revealed more details about its upcoming permanent retail destinations that were <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/12/23914796/netflix-house-retail-stores-2025\">first announced eight months ago</a>, including <a href=\"https://www.netflixhouse.com/\">where the first two Netflix House venues</a> will open in 2025: Dallas, Texas, and King of Prussia, Pennsylvania \u2014 a city located 15 miles outside of Philadelphia.</p>\n<p id=\"wArqOF\">The initial Netflix House locations will open in \u201ctwo of the most popular shopping centers in America,\u201d <a ", "id": 733585, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181027/netflix-house-retail-dallas-king-of-prussia-2025", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix House will fill the voids left by dead department stores", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T16:56:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3FDPahyop_ng6E8YmH-cARVc-8w=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414516/246965_vision_pro_AKrales_0246.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rF8xwL\">Apple may no longer be working on a new high-end Vision headset amid slowing sales of the Vision Pro, according to <a href=\"https://www.theinformation.com/articles/apple-suspends-work-on-next-high-end-headset-focused-on-releasing-cheaper-model-in-late-2025?rc=v4bmzs\">a new report from <em>The Information</em></a>. Instead, Apple has apparently been finding ways to reduce the cost of components for the first model and is working on a cheaper Vision headset that it aims to ship by the end of 2025.</p>\n<p id=\"Xj1UqB\">The first Vision Pro came out earlier this year, and while it\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24054862/apple-vision-pro-review-vr-ar-headset-features-price\">", "id": 733586, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24181106/apple-vision-pro-team-cheaper-headset", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s Vision Pro team is reportedly focused on building a cheaper headset", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T16:04:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The black Blink Video Doorbell hung up on a brick wall outside of a house.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hGCeeg0kAQCH0NAhdCmEpVgA9PY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414355/jtuohy_220222_5043_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The current promo means you won\u2019t have to pay extra for local storage.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vHRbrK\">\u2019Tis the season of travel, and if you want to beef up your home security ahead of your vacation, today might be a good time to do so. Right now, you can pick up a <strong>Blink Video Doorbell with a Sync Module 2</strong> at <a href=\"https://howl.me/cmupv4ibZKB\">Best Buy</a>, <a href=\"https://homedepot.sjv.io/c/482924/456723/8154?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.homedepot.com%2Fp%2FBlink-Video-Doorbell-Plus-Sync-Module-2-Battery-or-Wired-Smart-Wi-Fi-HD-Video-Doorbell-Camera-System-in-Black-B08SGC46M9%2F318917921&amp;sharedid=theverge.com\"", "id": 733587, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180106/amazon-blink-video-doorbell-anker-747-charger-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can grab a Blink Video Doorbell with a Sync Module 2 for just $42 right now", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T15:05:33+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OzN0PRpBk4yL6k_ZiQKywxw2Srk=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414176/ND_Lead.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ArBy3j\">After years of playing second fiddle to Link in her own franchise, Princess Zelda is finally getting a video game of her own this fall.</p>\n<p id=\"Zi5pjp\">During today\u2019s Direct presentation, Nintendo revealed <em>The Legend of Zelda</em>: <em>Echoes of Wisdom</em>, the franchise\u2019s first game to follow as Princess Zelda herself embarks on an adventure to save the world from destruction. After Ganon bests Link in battle, Zelda is left to her own devices to battle hordes of monsters that descend upon the game\u2019s take on Hyrule (which seems heavily inspired by 2019\u2019s <em>Link\u2019s Awakening </em>remake).</p>\n<p id=\"FQFm85\">According to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23721063/zelda-tears-", "id": 732178, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24180615/legend-of-zelda-echoes-of-wisdom-trailer-nintendo-direct", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Zelda is finally getting her own game", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T14:48:26+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The logo for Metroid Prime 4: Beyond.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MS2WgrcAYnp-QliI7quekQdb2aA=/0x167:2500x1834/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414118/ND_2.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"iYPxX5\">Nintendo finally shared gameplay footage of <em>Metroid Prime 4: Beyond</em> during Tuesday\u2019s Nintendo Direct. The brief video was classic <em>Metroid Prime</em>, featuring intense first-person gunfighting <em>and</em> scanning stuff in the environment. Unfortunately, we\u2019ll have to wait a little while until we can play it for ourselves, as the company gave a vague 2025 release window for the title. </p>\n<p id=\"nsq6Jr\">We\u2019ve been waiting a very long time for any scraps of information about the next entry in the beloved <em>Metroid Prime</em> series. The game was first revealed <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2017/6/13/15782806/metroid-prime-4-nintendo-switch-announced-e3-2017\">on June 1", "id": 732179, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23768041/metroid-prime-4-nintendo-direct-trailer", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo shares the first gameplay trailer for Metroid Prime 4: Beyond", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T14:25:20+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Mario &amp;amp; Luigi Brothership\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xpfft5pEByjbIs1_EFdgIECeXMI=/136x0:1636x1000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414089/Screenshot_2024_06_18_at_10.11.24_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"POpG8t\">To start off Nintendo\u2019s Summer Game Fest-adjacent Direct, the company debuted a new <em>Mario &amp; Luigi</em> game: <em>Mario &amp; Luigi: Brothership</em>.  It\u2019s been nine years since the last <em>Mario &amp; Luigi </em>game, <em>Bowser\u2019s Inside Story,</em> which debuted in 2009 on the Nintendo DS before being rereleased with extra content and a whole new side story on the 3DS in 2018.</p>\n<p id=\"Du50tI\">In <em>Brothership</em>, the Mario Bros commandeer their own sailing ship to explore an all-new world dotted with islands in their quest to return to the Mushroom Kingdom. The two must work together using their powers of brotherly love to ove", "id": 732180, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24180608/mario-and-luigi-brothership-release-date-nintendo-direct", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Mario & Luigi: Brothership is a brand-new Mario RPG for Switch", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Elden Ring\u2019s DLC Shadow of the Erdtree\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Inx7lq1IJ4dDMGOeF0xA5cZ5TeY=/188x0:2213x1350/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414016/elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_screenshot_03_en_28feb24_ezgif.com_webp_to_png_converter__1_.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: FromSoftware</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Playing Erdtree was a lesson in humility I needed.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24180536/shadow-of-the-erdtree-review-elden-ring-dlc\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 732182, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24180536/shadow-of-the-erdtree-review-elden-ring-dlc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Shadow of the Erdtree reintroduced me to Elden Ring by kicking my ass", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Beats Solo Buds next to a cocktail drink.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0eSN3Z1uP28IKLTrdp0pgM-1OKw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73414014/DSCF7463_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>There are clear tradeoffs \u2014 like a charging case with no extra battery juice \u2014 but the price and Beats\u2019 cultural cachet are likely enough to guarantee success for the Solo Buds.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24180840/beats-solo-buds-earbuds-hands-on\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 732181, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24180840/beats-solo-buds-earbuds-hands-on", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Beats Solo Buds have a great look and an even better price", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T13:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Nintendo\u2019s logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MGuknfYTrpXb1cQosff4TFxXdx0=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73413944/acastro_STK054_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>No Switch 2, no problem.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180183/nintendo-direct-june-2024-news-trailers\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 732183, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180183/nintendo-direct-june-2024-news-trailers", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo Direct June 2024: all the news and trailers", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T13:23:48+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of the shape of a brain on a circuit board.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/40dwPlpzIXNDqus7za8TijxQYzs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73413934/STK414_AI_CHATBOT_E.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"YDXn07\">Google DeepMind <a href=\"https://deepmind.google/discover/blog/generating-audio-for-video/\">has taken the wraps off</a> of a new AI tool for generating video soundtracks. In addition to using a text prompt to generate audio, DeepMind\u2019s tool also takes into account the contents of the video.</p>\n<p id=\"u0YrE6\">By combining the two, DeepMind says users can use the tool to create scenes with \u201ca drama score, realistic sound effects or dialogue that matches the characters and tone of a video.\u201d You can see some of the examples posted on DeepMind\u2019s website \u2014 and they sound pretty good.</p>\n<div id=\"lQQp0s\"><div", "id": 732184, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180854/google-deepmind-ai-video-pixels-text-prompts-generate-video-soundtracks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google DeepMind\u2019s new AI tool uses video pixels and text prompts to generate soundtracks", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T13:11:44+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Elon Musk over a Vergecast illustration.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/U1UP5XSpBvH-h7maDHQC5GamPWk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73413901/VRG_VST_0618_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bhbbSu\">Elon Musk <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/13/24177816/tesla-shareholder-elon-musk-pay-package-vote-news\">got paid</a>. A lot. Now comes the interesting part: Musk has to make Tesla so big, so successful, and so valuable that the tens of billions he\u2019s getting seem cheap by comparison. You might think selling cars is the way to get there, but you might be wrong about that. Musk and, by extension, Tesla seem far more interested in some much bigger, more ambitious, and decidedly more complicated ideas.</p>\n<p id=\"ai89lr\">On <a href=\"https://link.chtbl.com/vergecast\">this episode of <em>The Vergecast</em></a>, <em>The Verge</em>\u2019s Andrew Hawkin", "id": 732185, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180863/tesla-future-robots-ai-apple-watch-rest-days-vergecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tesla\u2019s big, epic, confusing future", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Jzn3KFDndNoA6VrxcP7pRa9VlYc=/102x0:897x530/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73413825/Blink_Moments_BackYard.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Blink\u2019s new Moments feature should make it easier to see relevant clips at a glance.</em> | Image: Blink</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pmSDCP\">Budget smart security camera company Blink is adding a neat trick to its app: <a href=\"https://support.blinkforhome.com/en_US/video-clips/moments\">Blink Moments</a> automatically stitches together relevant clips from multiple cameras into a single video. The idea is to make it easier to see what\u2019s been going on around your home and also to share it with friends and family \u2014 or the police \u2014 depending on what you captured.</p>\n<p id=\"KQpGys\">Moments, which has been in beta testing, started rolling out on June 4th and will be available to all Blink users with multiple cameras in the next few weeks, according to the comp", "id": 732186, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180359/blink-smart-security-camera-moments-cross-camera-tracking", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Blink and you won\u2019t miss these Moments", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-18T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the front and back of the Xreal Beam Pro.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/j9I